Process called "analyze_generated_code" that takes generator as CodeGenerator and code as GeneratedCode returns CodeAnalysis:
    Try:
        Let complexity_analyzer be generator.code_synthesizer.analyzers["complexity"]
        Let quality_analyzer be generator.code_synthesizer.analyzers["quality"]
        Let performance_analyzer be generator.code_synthesizer.analyzers["performance"]
        
        Let complexity be complexity_analyzer with code as code
        Let quality_score be quality_analyzer with code as code
        Let performance_score be performance_analyzer with code as code
        
        Let issues be list containing
        
        If complexity is greater than 10.0:
            Add CodeIssue with:
                issue_type as "high_complexity"
                severity as "warning"
                message as "Code complexity is high"
                location as CodeLocation with:
                    line as 0
                    column as 0
                    offset as 0
                    metadata as dictionary containing
                suggestions as list containing "Consider simplifying the code"
                metadata as dictionary containing
            to issues
        
        Return CodeAnalysis with:
            complexity as complexity
            size as length of code.content
            quality_score as quality_score
            issues as issues
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
    Catch error:
        Return CodeAnalysis with:
            complexity as 0.0
            size as 0
            quality_score as 0.0
            issues as list containing
            metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "complexity_code_analyzer" that takes code as GeneratedCode returns Float:
    Note: Complexity code analyzer implementation
    Return 0.0

Process called "quality_code_analyzer" that takes code as GeneratedCode returns Float:
    Note: Quality code analyzer implementation
    Return 1.0

Process called "performance_code_analyzer" that takes code as GeneratedCode returns Float:
    Note: Performance code analyzer implementation
    Return 1.0

Process called "generate_code_from_specification" that takes generator as CodeGenerator and spec as CodeGenerationSpecification returns GeneratedCode:
    Try:
        Let generator_function be generator.code_synthesizer.generators[spec.generation_type] if generator.code_synthesizer.generators contains spec.generation_type else default_code_generator
        
        Let generated_code be generator_function with spec as spec
        
        Return generated_code
        
    Catch error:
        Return GeneratedCode with:
            code_type as "error"
            content as "Code generation failed: " plus error.message
            ast as create_error_ast with message as error.message
            metadata as dictionary containing
            performance_metrics as dictionary containing

Process called "function_code_generator" that takes spec as CodeGenerationSpecification returns GeneratedCode:
    Note: Function code generator implementation
    Return GeneratedCode with:
        code_type as "function"
        content as "Generated function code"
        ast as ASTNode with:
            node_type as "function"
            value as None
            children as list containing
            position as Position with:
                line as 0
